<stack-static>
    <statement><p><p>
A student stands <m>{11}</m> m away from a building. The angle of elevation of the top of the building is <m>{30}</m><m>^{\circ}</m>. Find the height of the building.
</p>

<p>
Give your answer correct to <alert>2 decimal places</alert>.
</p>

<p>
Height = <fillin characters="8" name="ans1"/> m  
</p></p></statement>
    <solution><p><h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>
Step 1: Use the tangent ratio:
</p>

<p>
<me>
\tan \theta = \frac{\text{height}}{\text{distance}}
</me>
</p>

<p>
<me>
\tan {30} = \frac{h}{11}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 2: Solve for height:
</p>

<p>
<me>
h = {11} \times \tan {30}
</me>
</p>

<p>
<me>
h = {6.35} m
</me>
</p></p></solution>
    <answer><p><m>6.35</m></p></answer>
</stack-static>